  "text": "In the management literature, teams are hypothesised to provide benefits such as increased flexibility and creativeness, and are considered to be able to provide value because of the different perspectives and skills that the team members have [CITATION_1] . Teams are formed for a purpose or objective and this involves the attainment of one or more outcomes, such as designing new products or determining strategic direction [CITATION_2] .",
